  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technical Sales Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Masstron Pte Ltd is a Singapore-based engineering company providing <strong>fiber optic products and customised communication solutions</strong> for industrial sectors.</p><p>We are looking for a<strong> Technical</strong> <strong>Sales Engineer </strong>to support and grow our business through <strong>solution-based selling</strong>, working closely with engineers, project teams, and customers in the industry.</p><p>This role is suitable for candidates with technical or engineering experience who are interested in a <strong>performance-driven role</strong> with <strong>commission incentives</strong>, while remaining closely involved with engineering solutions and long-term customer relationships.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Engage customers to understand technical and operational requirements</p></li><li><p>Promote fiber optic products and customized communication solutions</p></li><li><p>Participate in technical discussions, customer meetings, and site visits</p></li><li><p>Prepare quotations, proposals, and basic technical documentation</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with internal engineering and operations teams</p></li><li><p>Follow up on enquiries, proposals, and ongoing projects</p></li><li><p>Develop and maintain long-term customer accounts</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Engineering, Electronics, Electrical, IT, or related field</p></li><li><p>3–8 years of relevant working experience<br />(engineering, technical support, project coordination, system integration, or similar roles)</p></li><li><p>Comfortable communicating with engineers and technical stakeholders</p></li><li><p>Willingness to learn sales, negotiation, and account development skills</p></li><li><p>Self-motivated with a results-oriented mindset</p></li></ul><h3>Remuneration Structure</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Base Salary + Commission</strong></p></li><li><p>Commission is tied to:</p><ul><li><p>Closed sales</p></li><li><p>Project value</p></li><li><p>Key account growth</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Clear and transparent incentive structure</p></li><li><p>Higher earnings linked directly to performance and contribution (uncapped, based on performance)</p></li></ul><h3>Training & Career Development</h3><ul><li><p>Structured training on fiber optic systems and solutions</p></li><li><p>Guidance on sales process, customer engagement, and proposal preparation</p></li><li><p>Career progression to Senior Sales Engineer / Technical Sales Manager</p></li></ul>",
